Subject: [PATCH 5/6] feat(brand-picker): emoji removal, fuzzy scoring,
 qty/brand extraction, topScore log
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Normalization:
- Strip \p{Extended_Pictographic} before all processing (handles 🛒 ✅ 🔥 etc.)

New functions:
- _bpParseQueryMeta(normQ): extracts {product, qty, brand} from normalized query
  "2 קוטג' תנובה" → {product:"קוטג'", qty:2, brand:"תנובה"}; qty stored for future use
- _levenshtein(a, b): O(m×n) with fast-exit when |len(a)-len(b)|>3

_bpScore improvements:
- Component 5: queryBrand boost (+20) when brand matches product name/brand field
- Component 6: fuzzy token scoring via Levenshtein — edit distance 1 = +12pts,
  distance 2 (for tokens ≥5 chars) = +6pts. Handles: ניר/נייר, טואלת/טואלט, קוטץ/קוטג

_bpRunSearch:
- Calls _bpParseQueryMeta to extract brand/qty, passes queryBrand to _bpScore
- Translation uses meta.product (brand/qty stripped) for cleaner OFX queries
- URL 2 condition fixed: enQuery !== normQ (was: !== rawQuery)
- _boldKeyword uses normQ (not raw query) for accurate keyword highlighting
- topScore computed for log; log renamed [search-quality] with topScore field

rawQuery still used for all display (UI header, modal text)

